                    <comment id="12577062" author="stefan@jira" created="Mon, 10 Mar 2008 16:38:45 +0000"  >the FileSystem interface is somehow &amp;#39;under-specified&amp;#39;, it doesn&amp;#39;t specify e.g. how to handle non-existing intermediate folders in above example.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
the currently existing other FileSystem implementations (local and db-based) silently create non-existing intermediate folders (just like java.io.File#mkdirs() does).&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
i&amp;#39;d suggest to mimic this behavior in MemoryFileSystem rather than throwing an exception.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
BTW: patches are welcome ;-)  </comment>
